<br>
Pets are quite workable on an efreeti raid, but there are some things to be aware of.<br>
<br>
Staging area #1: The death beetle room. No reason at all not to have a pet here. Perhaps the raid leader thinks your pet will break mez, since it is so crucial here?<br>
<br>
Pet pitfall #1: Crossing the lava. Kill the pet and levi across. Levitate everybody before crossing, it is really hard to get out once you fall in, and anybody falling in puts a damper on the raid.<br>
<br>
Staging area #2: Pulling 3 imps, plus the roaming guardian, to the ledge just past the lava. Again, pets are just fine here, but again mez is crucial.<br>
<br>
Pet pitfall #2: Fighting along the narrow ledge that leads to the efreeti is scary. Pets can fall off the ledge, or mobs can be pushed over the edge. Both are bad news, because the pit below is home to many mobs and a pet or imp over the side spells doom. I would kill my pet at Staging area #2, then bring up a new one on the ledge where you fight. Then kill the pet again. Don't try to get it to follow you up that ledge.<br>
<br>
Staging area #3: Inside the efreeti lord's room. Again, no reason not to have a pet here. We pull imps to the room for experience while waiting for the efreeti respawn. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 51st Trial<i><br>Member of Silmindo, Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#333333>(2/16/01 2:00:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets on Efreeti</span><hr size=1> <br>
I generally would avoid any raids where pets aren't allowed and there are no viable reasons why.<br>
<br>
What you end up dealing with is either (1) inexperienced leadership or (2) inexperienced raiding party.  Both will just end up getting you killed and you'll spend you raid on a long corpse run.   <br>
<br>
Saying no pets out on somethng like that just shows that there is some weak spot in the raid, in my opinion.   I'd tell the leader exactly that.  <br>
<br>
There are some places where you don't want pets out.  Most of the time, however, they are pefectly fine and most trains are caused by humans, not pets. <p> <br>
<b>Ez</b> <br>
