<br>
1)My guild did a Kael Raid. We cleared all the way from the EW side up to the arena. We would just plow our way through. I did not summon a pet here. Why? VI's pathing is as disgusting a fat french prostitue with only 3 toes. During the plow process I stuck to landing malo and keeping the 2 main tanks DSed (dont have group DS yet im only 51). Once we arrived at the spot to which we would be pulling to (and no longer running around) I summoned the minion and had no problem. <br>
<br>
The point of my story is why do mages get so offended when they are asked not to summon pets. Granted a mage's solo power is in his pet. A mage's power as a group member is not ALWAYS (notice I said not always) his pet. In a group we can offer: Bad arse dmg shields (plus a fire resist buff), MR debuffs and decent nukage. Pets are just not welcome in certain camps and I can understand why and I do not take offense to it. <br>
<br>
2) The fritos camp is basically tough because you break it down into 2 steps. A)Breaking in (do not bother with a pet here) B) Holding the camp. You can usually safely use a pet here, but the pathing is bad up there. Generally speaking in dungeons when we are moving i never use a pet once we are at pull spot I will then summon pet.  <p>***************************************************<BR>
