<br>
Efreeti pathing is fine!  Sure there are areas where pets do odd things, learn those spots and memorize Summon Companion for them.<br>
<br>
In Velious and in large encounters mages are reduced in the amount of nukage they can apply to a mob.  Sure the *numbers* look alot the same but a mages *actual* damage is far diminished.  A pet is an asset to your parties output, and a buffer for when things do go bad.<br>
<br>
Places I'm not familiar with I just watch my pet a little more closely than normal.<br>
<br>
The earlier posts are right, anyone saying 'no pets' are ignorant.  Even in places such as hate pets can be summoned safely and provide mana free dmg for your raid.<br>
